ontrolled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups (10 Reps × 3)","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Movement Early In The Day Helps Build Sleep Pressure, Making Sleep Easier At Night.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","This includes:","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can remain active in the body 6–8 hours, delaying sleep."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and reduce automatic, stress-driven reactions."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the voice instructions.","Allow the body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","Why this works","After the shower, the body experiences a natural drop in temperature, which signals the brain that it","is time for sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"exercise_routine","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","exercises":[{"name":"Once In Bed, Do This:","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Relax Your Forehead","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Relax Jaw And Tongue","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Drop Shoulders Completely","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Slowly Breathe Out","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Then Imagine A Calm Scene:","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"You Are Lying In A Quiet Meadow Under The Stars.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"The Night Air Is Cool And Peaceful.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Everything Around You Is Calm And Still.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Focus On This Scene While Breathing Slowly.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Day 7 Sleep Trick – The “dim Light Rule”","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"About 90 Minutes Before Sleep, Start Reducing Light Exposure In Your Environment.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 7?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 7 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced strengthening natural melatonin today."}]'::jsonb
