instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"20 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Pushups","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"15 Reps × 5 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Jumping Jacks","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"40 Reps × 4 Sets","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Standing Forward Stretch","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"12 Slow Repetitions","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]}]},{"type":"action_step","stepNumber":2,"title":"Caffeine Control Rule","instructions":["Follow this rule strictly:","No caffeine after 2 PM","This includes:","coffee","tea","energy drinks","pre-workout drinks","Caffeine can remain active in the body 6–8 hours, disturbing sleep cycles."],"whyThisWorks":"Small consistent actions reinforce stability and reduce automatic, stress-driven reactions."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Evening Nervous System Downshift","steps":["About 60 minutes before bed, listen to your guided sleep meditation audio.","Lie comfortably in bed.","Play the meditation audio at low volume.","Close your eyes and follow the instructions.","Allow the body to relax naturally.","Recommended length: 10–20 minutes."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"Body Temperature Sleep Trick","steps":["Take a warm shower 60–90 minutes before sleep.","Why this works","After the shower, the body temperature drops slightly, signaling the brain that it is time for sleep."],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"mindfulness_exercise","title":"The Military Sleep Method (fast Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying on a quiet beach at night.","You hear gentle waves and feel a cool breeze.","The night feels calm and peaceful.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 14 Sleep Trick – The “Digital Sunset Rule”","Screens are one of the biggest sleep disruptors.","Create a digital sunset 90 minutes before bedtime.","This means:","stop using phones","avoid social media","avoid bright laptop screens","avoid intense TV content","Instead, use this time for:","reading","stretching","listening to calm audio","preparing for sleep","Why this works","Screens emit blue light, which blocks melatonin production.","Reducing screen exposure before sleep allows the brain to naturally prepare for sleep.","Day 14 Goal","Lock in a stable sleep rhythm and protect the brain from late-night stimulation.","By the end of Week 2 many people notice:","feeling sleepy earlier at night","deeper sleep cycles","more consistent sleep timing","Day 2 – Building Early Sleep Pressure"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"exercise_routine","title":"Morning Sunlight Exposure (10–20 Minutes)","exercises":[{"name":"Within 30 Minutes Of Waking, Go Outside And Expose Your Eyes To Natural Daylight.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Step Outside Your Home, Balcony, Or Street.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Do Not Wear Sunglasses.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Face The Direction Of The Sky (not Directly At The Sun).","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},{"name":"Stay Outside For 10–20 Minutes.","instructions":["Perform with steady breathing and controlled pacing."]},