t Sleep Technique)","steps":["Once in bed, do this:","Relax your forehead","Relax jaw and tongue","Drop shoulders completely","Slowly breathe out","Then imagine a calm scene:","You are lying in a quiet valley under a clear night sky.","The air is cool and peaceful.","Everything around you is calm and silent.","Focus on the calm scene while breathing slowly.","Day 15 Sleep Trick – The “Nasal Breathing Trick”","Breathing through the nose instead of the mouth can significantly improve sleep quality.","When lying in bed:","keep your lips gently closed","breathe slowly through your nose","focus on calm, steady breathing","If needed, practice this for 3–5 minutes before sleep.","Why this works","Nasal breathing helps:","calm the nervous system","improve oxygen flow","reduce nighttime awakenings","It also encourages deeper and more stable sleep.","Day 15 Goal","Strengthen deep sleep recovery and physical fatigue, helping the body fall asleep faster and stay","asleep longer.","By Day 15 many people begin noticing:","stronger sleepiness at night","deeper sleep cycles","improved morning energy"],"completionMessage":"Stay with the practice until your body and mind feel steadier."},{"type":"journal","prompt":"What helped you most on Day 15?","helperText":"Write one or two practical observations.","followUpPrompt":"What will you repeat tomorrow?"},{"type":"close","message":"Day 15 is complete.","secondaryMessage":"You reinforced boosting deep sleep recovery today."}]'::jsonb
